1
00:00:02,001 --> 00:00:03,300
How much?

2
00:00:03,300 --> 00:00:05,000
Sixty-nine cents.

3
00:00:05,001 --> 00:00:07,000
And the gas?

4
00:00:07,001 --> 00:00:10,000
Y'all getting any rain up your way?

5
00:00:10,001 --> 00:00:12,000
What way would that be?

6
00:00:12,001 --> 00:00:15,000
I've seen you was from Dallas.

7
00:00:16,201 --> 00:00:18,300
What business is it of yours?

8
00:00:18,300 --> 00:00:20,000
Where I'm from?

9
00:00:20,801 --> 00:00:23,000
Friend-o?

10
00:00:24,401 --> 00:00:26,000
I didn't mean nothing by it.

11
00:00:26,001 --> 00:00:28,000
Didn't mean nothing.

12
00:00:28,001 --> 00:00:31,000
Just passing the time.

13
00:00:31,300 --> 00:00:36,000
If you don't want to accept that, I
don't know what else I can do for you.

14
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Will there be something else?

15
00:00:40,001 --> 00:00:42,000
I don't know. Will there?

16
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:49,000
There's something wrong.

17
00:00:49,001 --> 00:00:50,000
With what?

18
00:00:50,001 --> 00:00:52,000
With anything.

19
00:00:52,750 --> 00:00:54,000
Is that what you're asking me?

20
00:00:55,201 --> 00:00:57,300
Is there something wrong with anything?

21
00:00:57,300 --> 00:00:59,000
Will there be anything else?

22
00:00:59,001 --> 00:01:00,041
You already asked me that.

23
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Well, I need to see about closing then.

24
00:01:06,001 --> 00:01:07,000
See about closing?

25
00:01:07,001 --> 00:01:08,000
Yes, sir.

26
00:01:08,001 --> 00:01:09,000
What time do you close?

27
00:01:09,001 --> 00:01:10,000
Now. We close now.

28
00:01:10,801 --> 00:01:12,600
Now is not a time. What time do you close?

29
00:01:13,001 --> 00:01:15,000
Generally around dark, at dark.

30
00:01:19,550 --> 00:01:21,000
You don't know what
you're talking about, do you?

31
00:01:21,001 --> 00:01:22,000
Sir?

32
00:01:24,201 --> 00:01:28,400
I said, you don't know
what you're talking about.

33
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,000
What time do you go to bed?

34
00:01:31,901 --> 00:01:32,200
Sir?

35
00:01:32,901 --> 00:01:34,000
You're a bit deaf, aren't you?

36
00:01:34,001 --> 00:01:36,000
I said, what time do you go to bed?

37
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Somewhere around 9.30.

38
00:01:42,001 --> 00:01:44,000
I'd say around 9.30.

39
00:01:44,001 --> 00:01:45,000
I could come back then.

40
00:01:45,001 --> 00:01:47,000
Why would you be coming back?

41
00:01:47,001 --> 00:01:48,000
We'll be closed.

42
00:01:48,001 --> 00:01:49,000
Yeah, you said that.

43
00:01:49,001 --> 00:01:53,000
Well, I got to close now.

44
00:01:53,001 --> 00:01:55,000
You live in that house on the back?

45
00:01:56,100 --> 00:01:58,000
Yes, I do.

46
00:01:58,001 --> 00:02:00,000
Have you lived here all your life?

47
00:02:01,900 --> 00:02:05,000
This is my wife's
father's place originally.

48
00:02:08,901 --> 00:02:09,900
You married into it?

49
00:02:09,901 --> 00:02:12,000
We lived in Temple, Texas for many years.

50
00:02:12,001 --> 00:02:17,000
Raised a family there in Temple.

51
00:02:17,901 --> 00:02:20,000
We come out here about four years ago.

52
00:02:20,701 --> 00:02:21,000
You married into it?

53
00:02:22,701 --> 00:02:23,800
That's the way you want to put it.

54
00:02:24,501 --> 00:02:26,000
I don't have some way to put it.

55
00:02:27,201 --> 00:02:29,200
That's the way it is.

56
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:40,000
What's the most you
ever lost on a coin toss?

57
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:41,000
Sir?

58
00:02:41,001 --> 00:02:44,000
The most you ever lost on a coin toss?

59
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,000
I don't know.

60
00:02:47,001 --> 00:02:48,001
I couldn't say.

61
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:52,000
Call it.

62
00:02:52,701 --> 00:02:53,000
Call it?

63
00:02:53,001 --> 00:02:54,000
Yes.

64
00:02:54,001 --> 00:02:55,000
For what?

65
00:02:55,001 --> 00:02:56,001
Just call it.

66
00:02:59,100 --> 00:03:02,900
Well, we need to know
what we're calling it for here.

67
00:03:03,001 --> 00:03:04,000
You need to call it.

68
00:03:04,001 --> 00:03:06,000
I can't call it for you.

69
00:03:06,001 --> 00:03:08,000
Well, it wouldn't be fair.

70
00:03:08,001 --> 00:03:09,000
I didn't put nothing up.

71
00:03:09,001 --> 00:03:11,000
Yes, you did.

72
00:03:11,001 --> 00:03:13,000
You've been putting it up your whole life.

73
00:03:13,001 --> 00:03:14,001
You just didn't know it.

74
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:17,900
You know what date is on this coin?

75
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:18,700
No.

76
00:03:18,701 --> 00:03:19,700
1958.

77
00:03:20,401 --> 00:03:23,000
It's been traveling 22 years to get here.

78
00:03:23,001 --> 00:03:25,000
And now it's here.

79
00:03:25,001 --> 00:03:27,000
And it's either heads or tails.

80
00:03:28,101 --> 00:03:28,900
What do you have to say? Call it.

81
00:03:29,901 --> 00:03:30,000
Well, look.

82
00:03:30,001 --> 00:03:32,300
I need to know what I stand to win.

83
00:03:32,801 --> 00:03:33,801
Everything.

84
00:03:34,900 --> 00:03:35,300
How's that?

85
00:03:36,001 --> 00:03:37,000
You stand to win everything.

86
00:03:37,001 --> 00:03:38,001
Call it.

87
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,000
All right.

88
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,000
Head's in.

89
00:03:50,201 --> 00:03:51,400
Well done.

90
00:03:53,901 --> 00:03:55,000
Don't put it in your pocket, sir.

91
00:03:55,801 --> 00:03:56,500
Don't put it in your pocket.

92
00:03:57,100 --> 00:03:58,099
It's your lucky quarter.

93
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,099
Where do you want me to put it?

94
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:02,199
Anywhere. Not in your pocket.

95
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:08,409
Well, it'll get mixed in with the
others and become just a coin.

96
00:04:11,001 --> 00:04:12,000
Which it is.

